messages.messageBody:
My son finally added his, my DH and I thought he had ignored the subject all
together...

A mermaid
A dragon (he says even a small one is kind of big and counts for two seats
A fairy (or a few since they are small)
Bart (Simpson)
Sponge Bob
Arthur Dent (Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy)

Also, he would not invite Garfield because he would eat all the food and
there would be none for anyone else.

From: Elissa Jill Cleaveland <MystikMomma@...>
<<Mark Twain is a favorite person - if there is anyone I would want to meet
living or dead it would be him.>>

OOOH!! Let's play the dinner party game!
You have a table that seats eight, who are the 7 people, living or dead,
that you would invite over for dinner?

-=-=-=-
My dining room table seats 12:

Robin Williams, comedian
Benjamin Franklin
Homer (NOT Doh!-Homer---the poet! Gutterheads! <g>)
Leonardo DaVinci
Mark Twain
John Holt
Jeff McBride, magician
Helen Keller
Annie Rogers Clark, dog judge
Augustus Caesar
Danny Schmidt, singer/songwriter who *may* be here for supper and a house concert soon!

~Kelly

messages.messageBody:
>>>>>OOOH!! Let's play the dinner party game!
You have a table that seats eight, who are the 7 people, living or dead,
that you would invite over for dinner?>>>>

I'm assuming we're talking about famous people because if not, I'd pick
my family. :-)

1. Marquis de Sade
http://www.kirjasto.sci.fi/desade.htm
2. Midori
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midori_%28author%29
3. Sully Erna (from Godsmack) He would have to stay for dessert. ;-)
http://www.smackfans.com/
4. Steven Tyler (from Aerosmith) just so I could tell him that an
interview with him on his drug abuse, helped me with mine.
http://www.steven-tyler.net/
5. Chris Cornell (second helping of dessert)
http://www.chriscornell.com/main.html
6. Richrad Kern
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Kern
7. Ron Jeremy
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ron_Jeremy

Sounds like a fun evening to me. ;-)

~ Joanne ~

http://anunschoolinglife.blogspot.com/
